- Phrase 1 (mm.1-7): Stately, slower-moving texture. Whole-note and
  half-note block chords in LH (open root-pos "33"). RH dyads only —
  light, reserved. Reflects the awe in "God Himself is present."
- Phrase 2 (mm.8-14): Repeat with build. RH broken arpeggios (broken
  "33" in m.8); LH gains 4th note by m.9. Climax of phrase 2 in
  m.13 uses 3-note RH + 4-note LH simultaneously.
- Phrase 3 (mm.15-22): High melody reaches D5 in mm.19,21. RH
  extends up to G5 in m.15 arpeggio. LH uses "333" (7th) voicing
  in m.17 (V7) for richness before final I. Last two measures use
  ii→I (Am→G) with 4-3 suspension in RH.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- mm.4/11 (Em→Bm): B is common tone, held; E moves to F# (step up),
  G stays in LH; inner voice D moves to F# (third). Clean.
- m.19 (D→IV in one bar): LH drops a P5 D2→C2, natural bass walk.
- mm.21-22 (V→ii→I): Approaching final with ii (Am7) before resolving
  to I. RH A4-E4 (Am) → D4-G4 (I) is stepwise contrary to LH.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm.1-7: Sparse, stately (2+3 notes). Whole/half block chords.
- mm.8-14: Building (3+4 notes). RH arpeggio, LH fuller voicings.
- mm.15-22: Full, energetic (3+4 notes). High RH, contrary motion.
  Final mm.22 settles to root position with balanced I chord.
============================================================ -->
